President Obama recognizes the importance of small businesses in the American economy and emphasizes their role in creating jobs and supporting millions of Americans. He highlights that small businesses represent the American spirit of hard work and innovation, and his administration has taken steps to support them, including tax cuts and loans through the Small Business Administration. However, he acknowledges that more needs to be done, and his administration will continue to invest in infrastructure, support access to credit, and reform the immigration system to help businesses succeed. The President reaffirms his commitment to helping small businesses hire more workers, sell more products, and contribute to the growth of the American economy.